Body length 2.1–2.5. Pronotum distinctly longer than median head length. Hemelytron (
Fig. 1D
) with indistinct longitudinal markings.

Males: fore femur with row of seven spines on proximal third ventrally; fore tibia without spine (
Fig. 2H
); palar claw, median lobe of sternite VII and free lobe (
Fig. 2I
) as in diagnosis of 

Ctenonecta

. Left paramere: shaft stout, apex blunt (
Fig. 2K
). Right paramere: shaft broad at base, constricted at distal half, then expanded and constricted again before narrowly rounded apex; basal lobe with a distinct hump on mesial side, near base of shaft (
Fig. 2J
).

Vietnam : Lao Cai , Hanoi , Ha Tinh ( Wróblewski 1962 , 1967 ); first records for Cao Bang , Phu Tho , Quang Nam . Other countries: Thailand , China ( Nieser 2000 ;
Nieser et al. 2005
).
